      "writtenOn": "2026-05-21T08:07:34Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Hi Jeremy and Matt,\n\nThanks for the review. Currently, I am consuming it by manually allocating the binding struct using calloc in my application code, like this:\n\nmctp_dev-\u003ei2c \u003d calloc(1, sizeof(struct mctp_binding_i2c));\nmctp_i2c_setup(mctp_dev-\u003ei2c, ...);\n\nBecause of this approach, I indeed need the size definition of struct mctp_binding_i2c to be exposed.\n\nHowever, I totally agree with Matt\u0027s point. It would be much cleaner to encapsulate the allocation within the library by introducing mctp_i2c_init() and mctp_i2c_destroy() (similar to mctp_serial_init()). This way, the caller doesn\u0027t need to know the struct size.\n\nI will update the patchset to include mctp_i2c_init() and mctp_i2c_destroy() in i2c.c to improve the API. Does that sound good?",
      "parentUuid": "a76d9cc3_c1b8727a",
      "revId": "7ea7615b5ce6a73432b7e51f804260c4f971dbdb",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
